MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience managing, supervising, administering, advising on or delivering human resources management products or services equivalent to the next lower grade level (GS-12) or pay band in the federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector. Specialized experience must demonstrate performing duties such as the following:
1) Administering civilian human resources management programs;
2) Carrying out HR functions related to staffing, compensation, classification, employee relations, strategic workforce planning, or labor relations;
3) Interpreting and applying classification standards/guides to reach sound classification decisions;
4) Providing guidance on approaches to pay and compensation;
5) Providing strategic HR advice and guidance to senior management in order to execute HR plans. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management web site: https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series Experience refers to paid and unpaid experience, including volunteer work done through National Service programs (e.g., professional, philanthropic, religious, spiritual, community, student, social). Volunteer work helps build critical competencies, knowledge, and skills and can provide valuable training and experience that translates directly to paid employment.
